I"¸<h1 id="what-is-a-loop">What Is a Loop?</h1>

<p>Loops are used to iterate until a defined condition is reached.</p>

<p><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sangam14/RustLabs/master/img/intro_loop.png" alt="" /></p>

<h1 id="types-of-loops">Types of Loops</h1>
<p>There are two types of loops in Rust:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Definite Loops :- Loops in which the number of iterations is known at compile time.</p>
  </li>
  <li>Example
    <ul>
      <li>for</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Indefinite Loops  :- Loops in which the number of iterations is not known at compile time.</p>
  </li>
  <li>Example
    <ul>
      <li>while</li>
      <li>loop</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

